, Thailand aims to peak its greenhouse gas emissions in 2030, with the ambition to move towards net-zero greenhouse gas emissions as early as possible within the second half of this century, and towards carbon neutrality by 2065","page":"ii"},{"doc_id":43718,"document":"Second Generation NDC","version":"NDC 2.0","doc_type":"NDC","status":"Archived","area":"Overall mitigation target","scope":"Overall mitigation target","ghg":"GHG","type":"GHG: BAU","conditionality":"Unconditional","year":2030,"content":"Thailand intends to reduce its greenhouse gas emissions by 30 percent from the projected business-as-usual (BAU) level by 2030.","page":1},{"doc_id":43718,"document":"Second Generation NDC","version":"NDC 2.0","doc_type":"NDC","status":"Archived","area":"Overall mitigation target","scope":"Overall mitigation target","ghg":"GHG","type":"GHG: BAU","conditionality":"Conditional","year":2030,"content":"Thailand intends to reduce its greenhouse gas emissions by 30 percent from the projected business-as-usual (BAU) level by 2030. The level of contribution could increase up to 40 percent, subject to adequate and enhanced access to technology development and transfer, financial resources and capacity building support.","page":1},{"doc_id":43718,"document":"Second Generation NDC","version":"NDC 2.0","doc_type":"NDC","status":"Archived","area":"Net zero target","scope":"Overall mitigation target","ghg":"GHG","type":"GHG: Trajectory","conditionality":"Unclear conditionality","year":2065,"content":"Furthermore, Thailand will continue vigorous efforts in its challenge to meet the long-term goal of carbon neutrality by 2050 and net-zero greenhouse gas emission by 2065.","page":1},{"doc_id":32518,"document":"LTS","version":"LTS 1.1","doc_type":"LTS","status":"Active","area":"Overall mitigation target","scope":"Overall mitigation target","ghg":"GHG","type":"GHG: Fixed level","conditionality":"Unconditional","year":2050,"content":"carbon neutrality in 2050 (0 CO2) and net zero GHG emi